HEADWORD: Apopemptic
<hw>Ap`o*pemp"tic</hw> <pr>(-p⟦ecr⟧mp"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'apopemptiko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>'apope`mpein</grk> to send
off or away; <grk>'apo`</grk> from + <grk>pe`mpein</grk> to send.]</ety>
<def>Sung or addressed to one departing; valedictory; <as>as,
<ex>apopemptic</ex> songs or hymns</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

